# .gitattributes - line-ending policy for this repo.
#
# Added in V5.3 after a real failure: the user ran `bash sync_workshop.sh`
# during release staging and got
#     sync_workshop.sh: line 9: $'\r': command not found
#     : invalid option namee 10: set: pipefail
# because git's global core.autocrlf=true had checked the script out with
# CRLF terminators, and bash treats the trailing \r as part of each command.
# Without a .gitattributes this recurs on every checkout of every shell
# script, so the policy is pinned here rather than left to each machine's
# git config.
#
# * text=auto  : git decides text vs binary and stores LF in the repo.
#                Working-tree endings still follow core.autocrlf, so .bat
#                files keep their native CRLF on Windows.
# *.sh eol=lf  : shell scripts are checked out with LF ALWAYS, on every
#                platform, because bash cannot parse them otherwise.
#
# Nothing here forces CRLF on anything.

* text=auto
*.sh text eol=lf
